free_txt: LAHET, CEM95, CEM2K, CASCADE, INUCL and YIELDX
codes-simulated yields.
The experimental errors are within approx. 6-35%.
The errors in the independent and cumulative yields of
the reaction products for separate gamma-lines, were
determined using the error transfer formulas.
The uncertainties in the nuclear data-absolute values
of gamma-abundances and monitor reaction cross section
were found in the relevant analysis to make the major
contribution to the total error.
ITEP U-10 synchrotron was used.
Tc-99, isotopic composition:
Tc-99 more 99.9999%, Tc-97 less 10.E-04%, Tc-98 less
10.E-04%, was used.

Data was reported in final project technical
report of ISTC 839B-99 by yu.Titarenko and partially
corrected by author. Revised version does not contain
new data.
By yu.E.Titarenko.
The uncertainty are given in data Table 12
of ISTC-839B.  Detailed analysis see in the report.
-By compiler. If a nucleus has isomer state, but data
heading "ISOMER" contains space only, production cross
section includes isomer state production too.
.The uncertainty is given in data table.
- By author. Cumulative cross section is usual sum of
a nuclide independent cross section and cumulative
cross section of pregnitor.
Production cross sections for V-48, Ga-66, Rb-79, Cu-60
are "supracumulative" cross sections. Total
determination of the cross section see in REFERENCE.
.The uncertainty is given in data table.
